Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (peeling optional).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Cut the @tomato{1}(cut into 2cm cubes).

Drain the @grilling cheese{200%g}. Halve horizontally then slice into 1cm thick batons. Pop into a #bowl{} of cold water.

Place your hand on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%g}. Slice through horizontally to make two steaks.

> Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh.

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the onion until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the tomato, @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}, @sriracha{2%sachets}, @honey{1%sachet} and @water{50%ml}.

> For 4p, double the water.

Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked, season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

> Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if you feel it's become too thick.

Drizzle the chicken steaks with @oil{to taste} then season with @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet}, salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the chicken steaks until golden brown and cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove from the pan, cover and set aside.

> Cook in batches if your pan is getting overcrowded.

Remove the cheese from the water and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

In a bowl, beat @egg{1}.

> For 4p, double the eggs.

To a #small plate{}, add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}.

Toss the cheese sticks first in the egg, then in the breadcrumbs.

Return the pan to high heat with enough @oil{to taste} to completely coat the bottom.

Once hot, carefully lay the breaded cheese into the pan and fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn every ~{1-2%minutes}, adjusting the heat as needed.

When everything is almost ready, pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once warmed, spread a little @aioli{1%sachet} over the cut side of each bun.

Divide chicken steaks between base buns, drizzle over the sweet and spicy sauce then close with top bun.

Plate the potato wedges and golden fried cheese sticks alongside.

Use any remaining aioli for dipping.